==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chipmunk
<hw>Chip"munk`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Indian
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A squirrel-like animal of the genus
<gen>Tamias</gen>, sometimes called the <altname>striped
squirrel</altname>, <altname>chipping squirrel</altname>,
<altname>ground squirrel</altname>, <altname>hackee</altname>. The
common species of the United States is the <spn>Tamias
striatus</spn>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>chipmonk</asp>,
<asp>chipmuck</asp>, and <asp>chipmuk</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>chipped</ent>⟦br⟧
